rubrics.after#divGraduale: <Allelúia.> is not repeated. The <Glória in excélsis.> is said here.

rubrics.before#divGraduale: After each Lesson, the Cantor intones <Allelúia.>  The Choir continues the Chant, without repeating the intonation.  <Allelúia.> is not repeated at the end of the Verse.

mass_holy_pope.title: Mass of a Holy Pope
mass_holy_pope.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima the previous Alleluia is omitted and this Tract is sung.
mass_holy_pope.alPaschRubric: In Paschal Time the previous Alleluia is sung, then this one.

mass_i_martyr_not_bishop.title: Mass I of a Martyr not a Bishop
mass_i_martyr_not_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.

mass_one_martyr.title: Mass of one Martyr (in Paschal Time)

mass_ii_confessor_not_bishop.title: Mass II of a Confessor not a Bishop
mass_ii_confessor_not_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.
mass_ii_confessor_not_bishop.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the Gradual Os justi--> is omitted. Instead one sings the first Alleluia Beatus vir then this second Alleluia.

mass_doctors.title: Mass of Doctors
mass_doctors.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.
mass_doctors.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the Gradual Os justi--> is omitted. Instead one sings the first Alleluia Amavit eum Dominus then this second Alleluia.

mass_i_virgin_not_martyr.title: Mass I of a Virgin not a Martyr
mass_i_virgin_not_martyr.alPaschRubric: Paschal Time: Alleluia Adducentur regi virgines above, then this Alleluia.

mass_i_confessor_not_bishop.title: Mass I of a Confessor not a Bishop
mass_i_confessor_not_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.
mass_i_confessor_not_bishop.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the Gradual Justus (ut palma)--> is omitted. Instead one sings the first Alleluia Beatus vir then this second Alleluia.

mass_iii_two_or_more_martyr.title: Mass III of two or more Martyrs
mass_iii_two_or_more_martyr.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima the previous Alleluia is omitted and this Tract is sung.

mass_ii_martyr_bishop.title: Mass II of a Martyr-Bishop
mass_ii_martyr_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.

mass_ii_virgin_martyr.title: Mass II of a Virgin Martyr

mass_i_confessor_bishop.title: Mass I of a Confessor Bishop
mass_i_confessor_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.
mass_i_confessor_bishop.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the Gradual Ecce (sacerdos magnus)--> is omitted. Instead one sings the first Alleluia Tu es sacerdos then this second Alleluia.

mass_abbots.title: Mass of Abbots
mass_abbots.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.
mass_abbots.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the Gradual Domine (praevenisti)--> is omitted. Instead one sings the first Alleluia Justus ut palma then this second Alleluia.

epiphany.title: 6 Jan - The Epiphany of Our Lord

mass_i_two_or_more_martyr.title: Mass I of two or more Martyrs
mass_i_two_or_more_martyr.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima the previous Alleluia is omitted and this Tract is sung.

mass_i_martyr_bishop.title: Mass I of a Martyr-Bishop
mass_i_martyr_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.

mass_i_virgin_martyr.title: Mass I of a Virgin Martyr
mass_i_virgin_martyr.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima this Tract replaces the previous Alleluia.

mass_ii_martyr_not_bishop.title: Mass II of a Martyr not a Bishop
mass_ii_martyr_not_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.

mass_holy_woman_not_martyr.title: Mass of a Holy Woman not a Martyr
mass_holy_woman_not_martyr.trSeptRubric: Important note: for a Holy Woman not a Martyr the ending words of the first verse are omitted: pro cujus amore sanguinem tuum fudisti = « for the love of whom thou didst shed thy blood ». Obviously.
mass_holy_woman_not_martyr.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the previous Alleluia is sung then this one.

mass_holy_woman_martyr.title: Mass of a Holy Woman Martyr
mass_holy_woman_martyr.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima this Tract replaces the previous Alleluia.
mass_holy_woman_martyr.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the previous Alleluia is sung then this one.

mass_ii_confessor_bishop.title: Mass II of a Confessor Bishop
mass_ii_confessor_bishop.trSeptRubric: Sung after Septuagesima instead of the previous Alleluia.
mass_ii_confessor_bishop.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the Gradual is omitted. Instead one sings the first All. Juravit Dominus then this second Alleluia.

mass_bvm.title: Mass of the Blessed Virgin Mary
mass_bvm.alExtraRubric: In Advent the previous Alleluia is replaced by this one.
mass_bvm.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima this Tract replaces the Alleluia.
mass_bvm.alPaschRubric: During Paschal Time the Gradual is omitted, this Alleluia is sung then All. Ave Maria.

mass_dedication_church.title: Mass of the Dedication of a Church
mass_dedication_church.trSeptRubric: After Septuagesima this Tract replaces the previous Alleluia.
mass_dedication_church.alPaschRubric: In Paschal time the previous Alleluia is sung then this one.
